`length` is also an input so changing 
```
@set_module('mxnet.numpy_extension')
def softmax(data, axis=-1, length=None, temperature=None, use_length=False, dtype=None):
```
to 
```
@set_module('mxnet.numpy_extension')
def softmax(data, length=None, axis=-1, temperature=None, use_length=False, dtype=None):
```

## Description ##
FullyConnected operator could be fused with element wise sum operation in OneDNN. This change introduced fusing quantized FC + sum for BERT model when FC output is left as floating point.

For examples it converts following graph:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58251767/124464480-89b26400-dd94-11eb-859e-18a20371f597.png)
to:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58251767/124464536-9931ad00-dd94-11eb-8e04-5abdcd5dccbc.png)

Measurement of [test](https://gist.github.com/anko-intel/4c285456c97807dd49ab76112b905296)  similar to of the short fragment of BERT model  on AWSc5.24xlarge gives following results:
